<Link id="l01286" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1286"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Add 1 to the start/end of the EH clause; the IP associated with a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01287" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1287"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// call when the runtime does its scan is the IP of the next instruction</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01288" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1288"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (the one to which control will return after the call), so we need</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01289" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1289"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to add 1 to the end of the clause to cover that offset.  We also add</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01290" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1290"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 1 to the start of the clause to make sure that the ranges reported</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01291" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1291"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// for all clauses are disjoint.  Note that we&#39;ll need some additional</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01292" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1292"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// logic when machine traps are supported, since in that case the IP</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01293" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1293"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// that the runtime uses is the offset of the faulting instruction</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01294" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1294"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// itself; if such an instruction immediately follows a call but the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01295" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1295"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// two belong to different clauses, we&#39;ll need to insert a nop between</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01296" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1296"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// them so the runtime can distinguish the point to which the call will</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01297" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1297"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// return from the point at which the fault occurs.</span></CodeLine>
